Seven people have been killed and fourteen injured after a head on collision between a taxi and truck on Friday in Luipaard Road intersection in Krugersdorp.According to ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring paramedics as well as other services, arrived on the scene and found that both the taxi and truck parked in the middle of the road.&#8220;The taxi was found to have sustained a large amount of damage in the collision.&#8220;While inspecting the scene the paramedics found several bodies lying inside the wrecked taxi.&#8220;Unfortunately, nothing could be done for the patients and they were declared dead on the scene. A number of the bodies lay trapped inside of the vehicle,&#8221; Meiring said.On the scene paramedics checked the patients to see the amount of damage done by the accident and found that approximately 14 people had sustained injuries ranging from minor to serious.All of the patients were transported to different hospitals in the area after they were treated for their injuries.&#8220;Local authorities were on the scene to close off the road as well as to begin their investigation,&#8221; he said.-TNA Reporter